        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a micrometer and a telescoping gauge to measure the bore in the beam. Rounding at the
                top and bottom edges of the bore is acceptable.
            </para>
            <para>Measure the bore in two positions at the centerline of the side of the beam between 1/2 inch (12.7mm)
                from the top of the bore and 1/2 inch (12.7mm) from the bottom of the bore. If the average measurement
                is more than the Beam Bore Maximum Diameter specification in
                <hotlnk xrefid="t0200502">Table 2</hotlnk>, replace the beam (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200517">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200517" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200517" filename="../figg02/G0200517.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Measuring the Bore</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Repeat the measurement in two more positions at the centerline of the front of the beam between 1/2
                inch (12.7mm) from the top of the bore and 1/2 inch (12.7mm) from the bottom of the bore. If the average
                measurement is more than the Beam Bore Maximum Diameter specification in
                <hotlnk xrefid="t0200502">Table 2</hotlnk>, replace the beam (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200517">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
